{
  "stem": "5810.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my hatred for Germans was very much there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had very mixed feelings about that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I, I said, Germany?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The place that I promised myself I would never see or never visit.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not in my lifetime.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said, well, why not?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe, being in the army, I can extract some revenge.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was very bitter, I still was very bitter in those days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I started to speak about it to then-- I did-- I had married in 1957.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it happened right after marriage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I spoke to my wife, who, by the way, had not found out yet that she also had been a hidden child.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's another story.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She thought that she belonged to the family that was her mother and father, they-- she thought biological, but she found out that her mother and father had been shot in Poland, and that she had been adopted by the family, but too young to know and found out later.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That-- well, the trauma of finding out at 18 or 19, I think she was, is what kind of broke up our marriage.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that's-- I'm digressing now.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyway, my-- I spoke about it with my family, about going to Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I-- they, they dissuaded me to do that they said, because the things that you might feel, the things that you might do, although you could get away with things like that during the war, is not something that you can do or get away with in peacetime.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And those things wouldn't be accepted.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And to make a long story short, I went to my company commander and told them that, I'll go.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm under orders to go, but the consequences, they'll have to understand.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
